HOUSE BILL 768
D4 6lr2852
CF SB 658
By: Delegates Simpson and Shetty
Introduced and read first time: February 4, 2026
Assigned to: Appropriations
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 2, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Department of Human Services – Benefits for Children in Custody – Alterations
3 FOR the purpose of altering certain provisions relating to the responsibilities of the
4 Department of Human Services as representative payee and fiduciary for certain
5 children committed to the custody of the Department; requiring the Secretary of
6 Human Services to establish and maintain a foster youth savings program to
7 conserve additional resources to assist youth in transitioning to independence,
8 subject to the availability of funds; and generally relating to children in the custody
9 of the Department of Human Services.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
11 Article – Family Law
12 Section 5–527.1
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
16 Article – Family Law
17 Section 5–527.1
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 (As enacted by Section 1 of this Act)
21 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
22 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
